Clove cigarettes, also known as kretek cigarettes, are a niche segment in the tobacco industry that continues to attract a dedicated consumer base. The market for clove cigarettes can be segmented based on type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of type, the market is divided into filtered clove cigarettes and unfiltered clove cigarettes. Filtered clove cigarettes offer a milder smoking experience compared to the intense flavor of unfiltered ones. When it comes to distribution channels, clove cigarettes are sold through both online and offline channels. Online sales are gaining traction due to the convenience and wider reach they offer to consumers. Offline sales predominantly occur through retail stores, convenience stores, hypermarkets/supermarkets, and other physical retail locations. Geographically, the clove cigarettes market is spread across regions such as North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East & Africa, with varying levels of consumption and regulatory environments.

